<paragraph blockId="1.[173,1128,363,624]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis. P-2 very enlarged, a large thin long projection in the ventral and a small projection in the distoventral. IV-L-5 shortened, ventral margin with one projection, proximal seta away from segment base and proximal seta bent forward and thinner than the central seta on the projection. The distoventral seta, which is located between the central seta and the tip of the segment, is thick and small. There is a long and thin seta above the distoventral seta and a small, thick and curved seta next to the long seta. IV-L-6 extremely enlarged and strong claws.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[173,1127,659,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Male. 
<typeStatus box="[302,404,659,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Holotype</typeStatus>
, in parentheses variability of the 
<typeStatus box="[770,875,660,681]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">paratypes</typeStatus>
given as mean (n = 3). Idiosoma enlarged anteriorly, narrowed posteriorly, L/W 370 (375) / 250 (253) (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1112,688,710]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[145,181,1552,1574]" captionTargetBox="[156,1068,789,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[155,1069,786,1530]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 3. Kongsbergia ermani sp. n., male a) idiosoma, ventral view b) idiosoma, dorsal view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734797/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 3 
<emphasis box="[1101,1112,688,709]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">b</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), lenses with three-pieces, preantenniform setae distance L 35 (36), mouth opening L/W 110 (112) / 75 (76) (
<figureCitation box="[329,398,746,768]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[145,181,1552,1574]" captionTargetBox="[156,1068,789,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[155,1069,786,1530]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 3. Kongsbergia ermani sp. n., male a) idiosoma, ventral view b) idiosoma, dorsal view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734797/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 3 
<emphasis box="[387,398,746,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">a</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), capitulum L 145 (147) (
<figureCitation box="[661,730,746,768]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,210,1488,1510]" captionTargetBox="[177,1125,780,1457]" captionTargetId="figure-199@3.[174,1126,776,1459]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 4. Kongsbergia ermani sp. n., male a) gnathosoma b) IV-L outside view c) IV-L inside view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734799" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5734799/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fig. 4 
<emphasis box="[719,730,746,767]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">a</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[173,1127,659,1142]" box="[234,1126,774,796]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
